# Build context exclusions for `podman/docker build -f container/Containerfile .`.
# Without these, ~300 MB of pre-built artifacts (the macOS .app, the Rust
# host target/ dir, captured PNGs) gets streamed to the daemon on every
# build.

.git
.gitignore

# Host-built native binaries. The container rebuilds Rust for linux/amd64
# anyway, and the .app is a desktop artifact that has nothing to do with
# the web export the container serves.
build/
sim-rust/target/

# Capture / preview outputs.
output/

# Host-built Godot web export. The container regenerates this from source
# in its godot-builder stage, so a local copy would just be a stale ghost
# silently overriding the fresh build.
shaders-godot/godot-project/web/build/

# OS / editor noise.
.DS_Store
.idea/
.vscode/

# Anything else the dev keeps locally.
*.swp
*.swo
